snippet: A Russian Proton-M rocket carrying a communications satellite crashed in Kazakhstan after what appeared to have been an engine malfunction, an official said.
abstract: Russian Proton-M rocket carrying sophisticated communications satellite crashes after takeoff, reviving questions over Russia's space program after series of failed launches in recent years.
lead_paragraph: A Russian Proton-M rocket carrying a communications satellite crashed in Kazakhstan after what appeared to have been an engine malfunction, an official said.
